from @Jackie-Jiang : 
> the real problem is that our scalar function (not implementing TransformFunction) is not able to return different type based on the argument, and the post-aggregation (e.g. group by date and return the result of a function on date) is using the scalar function instead of TransformFunction. This is a known issue, and we are exploring a fix

closing as duplicate.

@Jackie-Jiang Can you take a look into this? 

According to @mayankshriv and the previous PR https://github.com/apache/pinot/pull/10110 , it mentions that `In the offline flow, we already convert byte[] type to ByteArray for the MurmurPartition function to handle it correctly.`.

We were not able to find this part. Can you confirm on this?
